data.sampled:
The correct answer is: d) merge sort.

Merge sort uses two arrays, one for sorted elements and another empty array for storing unsorted elements. It splits a given list into its smallest components, sorts each component, then merges them back together in their original order. This method can be slower than other methods as it requires additional memory and more steps. However, it has the advantage of being stable, meaning that items will not move positions within their own group after they are sorted. Other algorithms like insertion or bubble sort may change positions within groups even though they are already sorted. Cycle sort is also stable because it does not require any swapping, but it only works on certain types of lists.
